This puzzle applies three independent conditions to an integer `n > 1000`. Part A performs a prime-factorization procedure and examines the resulting list. Part B converts `n` to a different base and applies a symmetry test. Part C extracts a classic digit property and runs a standard mathematical check on it. All three must hold simultaneously — finding numbers in the overlap of these three constraints is non-trivial. Good luck!

